"2010-07-20T19:26:38.670"	"2"	"35"	"A limit is the term used when you examine a function as it approaches some value. For example, the function f(x) = 1/x. You can take a limit of this function as x approaches infinity and as x approaches 0 and see what occurs, and get an idea of the behaviour of the function in these regions even though the function cannot be defined at the exact values you have taken limits of. (1/0 is undefined, and 1/infinity cannot be done without adding infinity to the number system - see the hyperreals for this)"	"d4ded071-3040-4a66-a8e2-503a53a7f4da"	"27"	"52"	""	""	""
