"2010-07-20T19:27:39.433"	"2"	"56"	"Indeed this is true. The underlying reason is that decimal numbers are not unique representations of the reals. (Technically, there does not exist a bijection between the set of all decimal numbers and the reals.)\r\n\r\nHere's a very simple proof:\r\n\r\n    1 / 3 = 0.333...\r\n\r\n    => 0.333 * 3 = 0.999... (multiplying each digit by 3)\r\n\r\n    But then we already know 0.333... * 3 = 1\r\n\r\n    Therefore 0.999... = 1\r\n"	"c4434417-d5ef-4f4b-8217-335b69ec3311"	"31"	"58"	""	""	""
