"2010-07-20T19:52:47.110"	"5"	"63"	"Assuming this is relative to the origin (as John pointed out): Given two position vectors p<sub>1</sub> and p<sub>2</sub> the dot product is:\r\n\r\n> p<sub>1</sub> * p<sub>2</sub> = |p<sub>1</sub>| *\r\n> |p<sub>2</sub>| * cos(v)\r\n\r\nSolving for v, we get:\r\n\r\n> v = arccos(p<sub>1</sub> * p<sub>2</sub> / (|p<sub>1</sub>| * |p<sub>2</sub>|))\r\n\r\nFor 2d space this equals:\r\n\r\n> v = arccos((x<sub>1</sub> * x<sub>2</sub> + y<sub>1</sub> * y<sub>2</sub>) / sqrt((x<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> + y<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup>) * (x<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup> + y<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup>)))\r\n\r\nAnd extended for 3d space:\r\n>  v = arccos((x<sub>1</sub> * x<sub>2</sub> + y<sub>1</sub> * y<sub>2</sub> + z<sub>1</sub> * z<sub>2</sub>) / sqrt((x<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> + y<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> + z<sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup>) * (x<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup> + y<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup> + z<sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup>)))"	"e37b08de-52ad-420b-ac1c-535279895d33"	"65"	"123"	"added 8 characters in body; deleted 9 characters in body; added 3 characters in body; added 20 characters in body"	""	""
