"2010-07-21T07:21:11.583"	"5"	"56"	"Indeed this is true. The underlying reason is that decimal numbers are not unique representations of the reals. (Technically, there does not exist a bijection between the set of all decimal numbers and the reals.)\r\n\r\nHere's a very simple proof:\r\n\r\n    1 / 3 = 0.333... (by long division)\r\n\r\n    => 0.333 * 3 = 0.999... (multiplying each digit by 3)\r\n\r\n    But then we already know 0.333... * 3 = 1\r\n\r\n    Therefore 0.999... = 1\r\n"	"bd7fd28c-2394-400e-8ac3-c1075e7df443"	"31"	"612"	"added 19 characters in body"	""	""
