"2010-07-21T12:56:10.100"	"2"	"73"	"Unambiguous names for the set of nonnegative integers (0, 1, 2, 3, ...) are **whole numbers** and $\\mathbb{N}_0$.  \r\nUnambiguous names for the set of positive integers (1, 2, 3, ...) are **counting numbers** and $\\mathbb{N}^+$.  \r\nAs other answers (and your own question) indicate, **natural numbers**, or $\\mathbb{N}$, can have different meanings, depending on context. If which usage you mean is not clear from context, you are better off using one of the other terms."	"4ef7a621-41ae-4ff3-8860-e3d7fa30b0ad"	"318"	"721"	""	""	""
