"2010-07-21T14:20:30.210"	"2"	"9"	"To follow up user80's answer, you want to get transformations of the form v --> Av + b, where A is a 3 by 3 matrix (the linear part of transformation) and b is a 3-vector.  We can encode this transformation in a 4 x 4 matrix by having putting A in the top left with three 0's below it and making the last column be (b,1).  Multiplying the 4-vector (v,1) with this matrix will give you (Av + b, 1)."	"76c391e0-6875-4baa-9cde-2203831942d1"	"340"	"767"	""	""	""
