"2010-07-22T03:11:57.567"	"2"	"536"	"The discriminant of any monic polynomial is the product $\\prod_{i \\neq j} (x_i - x_j)^2$ of the squares of the differences of the roots (in an algebraic closure, e.g. $C$). Cf. the [Wikipedia article][1] on this. Consequently, if the roots are all real and distinct, this must be positive.\r\n\r\n(If the polynomial is not monic, the factor $a_0^{2n-2}$ is thrown in, for $a_0$ the leading coefficient and $n$ the degree; this is positive for a real polynomial.)\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discriminant#Discriminant_of_a_polynomial"	"53c2f3c2-806d-42fd-8716-d5491229c689"	"433"	"996"	""	""	""
